 {"id":"rust_proxy-btn","title":"Implement dry-run for stop command","description":"## Implement Dry-Run for Stop Command

### Overview

Add --dry-run support to the stop command so users can see what would happen without actually stopping the daemon.

### User Experience

```bash
$ rp stop --dry-run
Would stop daemon process (PID: 12345)
Would remove PID file at /var/run/rp.pid
Would close 3 active connections

No changes made (dry-run mode)

$ rp stop -n  # short flag
Would stop daemon process (PID: 12345)
...
```

### Implementation

```rust
pub async fn stop_command(args: StopArgs) -> Result<()> {
    let ctx = if args.dry_run {
        Some(DryRunContext::new())
    } else {
        None
    };

    // Check if daemon is running
    let pid = match read_pid_file() {
        Ok(pid) => pid,
        Err(_) => {
            if args.dry_run {
                println!("Daemon is not running. Nothing to do.");
            }
            return Ok(());
        }
    };

    if let Some(ref ctx) = ctx {
        ctx.would_do(&format!("Stop daemon process (PID: {})", pid));
        ctx.would_do(&format!("Remove PID file at {}", pid_file_path().display()));

        // Check for active connections if possible
        if let Ok(conn_count) = get_active_connection_count(pid) {
            if conn_count > 0 {
                ctx.would_do(&format!("Close {} active connection(s)", conn_count));
            }
        }

        println!("{}", ctx.format());
        println!("\nNo changes made (dry-run mode)");
        return Ok(());
    }

    // Actual stop logic
    stop_daemon(pid).await?;
    remove_pid_file()?;
    println!("Daemon stopped");
    Ok(())
}
```

### CLI Integration

```rust
#[derive(Parser)]
pub struct StopArgs {
    /// Show what would happen without actually stopping
    #[arg(short = 'n', long)]
    pub dry_run: bool,

    /// Output in JSON format
    #[arg(long)]
    pub json: bool,
}
```

### JSON Output

```json
{
  "dry_run": true,
  "actions": [
    "Stop daemon process (PID: 12345)",
    "Remove PID file at /var/run/rp.pid",
    "Close 3 active connections"
  ],
  "would_affect": {
    "pid": 12345,
    "pid_file": "/var/run/rp.pid",
    "active_connections": 3
  }
}
```

